WEBVTT

00:00.200 --> 00:01.666
I've got another job,
if you're interested.

00:01.668 --> 00:03.468
Who's the buyer? Some
douchebag billionaire.

00:03.469 --> 00:04.937
Craig: They're moving the sculpture.
We already know the route.

00:04.939 --> 00:06.138
We're gonna hijack
the truck.

00:06.140 --> 00:08.407
Where's the money?
We don't get paid today.

00:08.409 --> 00:10.809
I can't go back to my family
without our money.

00:10.811 --> 00:12.210
Here's 40k.

00:12.212 --> 00:13.545
I'll have the rest
next week.

00:13.547 --> 00:14.546
[ Door opens ]

00:14.548 --> 00:15.880
Hey.
Renn: Hi.

00:15.882 --> 00:17.482
Can I crash here tonight?

00:17.484 --> 00:19.017
I'm not a part

00:19.019 --> 00:20.819
of your ghetto-ass
gang-runner bullshit.

00:20.821 --> 00:23.087
[ Gunshots ]

00:23.089 --> 00:25.357
[ Glass shatters ]

00:25.359 --> 00:27.159
Colby: Adrian's working
with Jack.

00:27.161 --> 00:28.560
You should have told me
he was your boyfriend.

00:28.562 --> 00:30.362
Deran Cody.
He's got a record.

00:30.364 --> 00:33.165
I had a crush on you
when we were kids.

00:33.167 --> 00:34.833
Spent the night
in the woods?

00:34.835 --> 00:35.968
Manny: Yeah, lemme guess.

00:35.970 --> 00:37.035
He thought somebody
was after him.

00:37.037 --> 00:38.370
Lou: He thought the VC
was coming in.

00:38.372 --> 00:39.371
Janine: That's right.

00:39.373 --> 00:41.774
Wait 'til he's gone
and then laugh at him.

00:41.776 --> 00:43.642
Colin makes you dangerous.

00:43.644 --> 00:44.777
Without him,

00:44.779 --> 00:48.380
you're just a bunch of
twitchy assholes with guns.

00:48.382 --> 00:49.848
Smurf!

00:49.850 --> 00:51.650
♪♪

00:51.652 --> 00:54.119
[ Sobs ]

00:55.322 --> 00:58.991
♪♪

00:58.993 --> 01:05.063
♪ She stares deeply ♪

01:05.065 --> 01:08.801
♪ Locked inside me ♪

01:08.803 --> 01:11.770
♪ Burnin' brightly ♪

01:14.809 --> 01:20.545
♪ One they know
that I cannot take ♪

01:20.547 --> 01:24.082
♪ Waitin' for it all to begin ♪

01:24.084 --> 01:27.086
♪ Every night now, they'll win ♪

01:31.091 --> 01:33.625
♪ Come and meet my black hole ♪

01:33.627 --> 01:37.696
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:37.698 --> 01:41.500
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:41.502 --> 01:45.370
♪ I've got a big black hole ♪

01:45.372 --> 01:49.574
♪ I've got a big black,
big black hole ♪

01:49.576 --> 01:53.311
♪ Got a big black hole
inside of me ♪

01:53.313 --> 01:55.380
♪ Got a ♪

01:55.382 --> 02:03.055
[ Engine runs ]

02:03.057 --> 02:05.924
Alright.
Hey. Pick a spot.

02:05.926 --> 02:07.926
Alright?
Watch your speed.

02:07.928 --> 02:09.461
Quarter turn on the wheel.

02:09.463 --> 02:11.396
Hit the e-brake
as you turn.

02:11.398 --> 02:12.931
Okay?
Yeah.

02:12.933 --> 02:15.534
[ Engine revs ]

02:15.536 --> 02:16.801
What are you waiting...
[ Tires squeal ]

02:16.803 --> 02:19.872
♪ Half moon, night time sky ♪

02:19.874 --> 02:24.409
♪ Seven stars, heaven's eyes ♪

02:24.411 --> 02:27.212
♪ Seven songs
from the seven seas ♪

02:27.214 --> 02:28.747
Yeah! [ Giggles ]

02:28.749 --> 02:31.349
♪ Just to bring all
your sweet love home to me ♪

02:31.351 --> 02:32.284
Again.

02:32.286 --> 02:33.485
[ Engine roars, tires squeal ]

02:33.487 --> 02:35.087
♪ Hey, you fill me like
the mountains ♪

02:35.089 --> 02:37.556
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

02:37.558 --> 02:40.559
♪ You fill me like the sea,
Lord ♪

02:40.561 --> 02:44.829
♪ Not coming past
but still at last ♪

02:44.831 --> 02:47.232
♪ You fill me like
the mountains ♪

02:47.234 --> 02:49.501
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

02:49.503 --> 02:51.904
♪ Bring it on home ♪

02:51.906 --> 02:55.039
♪ Love brings life to me ♪

02:55.041 --> 02:56.308
Oh, shit!

02:56.310 --> 02:58.376
[ Both exhale sharply ]

02:58.378 --> 02:59.311
Whoo!

02:59.313 --> 03:00.845
Oh, ho, ho.

03:00.847 --> 03:02.114
[ Breathes heavily ]

03:03.584 --> 03:05.517
[ Chuckles ]
[ Laughs ]

03:05.519 --> 03:07.519
Not bad.

03:07.521 --> 03:10.589
"Not bad" my ass.

03:10.591 --> 03:11.924
I was freaking perfect.

03:11.926 --> 03:12.925
Keep practicing.

03:12.927 --> 03:13.992
Should be easy,

03:13.994 --> 03:15.794
as much as you like
stealing cars.

03:15.796 --> 03:16.929
Hey, admit it.
Huh?

03:16.931 --> 03:19.731
I can drive.

03:19.733 --> 03:20.933
Yeah?

03:20.935 --> 03:23.602
How about when the cops
are chasing you?

03:23.604 --> 03:24.737
I drive faster.

03:24.739 --> 03:27.139
[ Engine revs ]

03:27.141 --> 03:30.075
[ Tires squeal ]

03:30.077 --> 03:31.676
Woman:
<i>Because it's made me</i>

03:31.678 --> 03:34.746
<i>a better, stronger,</i>
<i>healthier person.</i>

03:34.748 --> 03:36.348
<i>I can work</i>
<i>my waist, arms, abs...</i>

03:36.350 --> 03:38.150
Dr. Laffin: Mr. Cody?

03:38.152 --> 03:39.818
Want to come with me?

03:44.625 --> 03:47.626
Mr. Cody,
your mother was diagnosed

03:47.628 --> 03:50.763
with an aggressive
and advanced melanoma.

03:50.765 --> 03:52.598
She has... cancer.

03:54.701 --> 03:57.269
[ Sighs ]

03:58.172 --> 03:59.304
Are you supposed...

04:03.243 --> 04:04.843
are you supposed
to tell me this?

04:04.845 --> 04:06.378
She asked me to.

04:06.380 --> 04:08.847
I know
this is a lot to process,

04:08.849 --> 04:11.383
but we need to discuss
the next steps.

04:11.385 --> 04:16.454
♪♪

04:16.457 --> 04:17.656
Olivia:
<i>Her face gets all green,</i>

04:17.658 --> 04:19.791
<i>and then she pukes</i>
<i>all over my shoes.</i>

04:19.793 --> 04:22.594
<i>That bitch</i>
<i>cannot handle her booze.</i>

04:22.596 --> 04:23.928
<i>You're coming to study,</i>
<i>right?</i>

04:23.930 --> 04:25.730
Yeah.
<i>Awesome.</i>

04:25.732 --> 04:27.599
<i>I will text you</i>
<i>the address.</i>

04:27.601 --> 04:29.534
Great.
See you then.

04:29.536 --> 04:30.535
[ Cellphone beeps ]

04:30.537 --> 04:38.276
♪♪

04:38.278 --> 04:39.345
[ Slams door ]

04:41.415 --> 04:42.881
Is that what
you came here to do?

04:42.883 --> 04:45.217
That stunt that you pulled
at the house

04:45.219 --> 04:47.019
is gonna cost me
20 grand.

04:47.021 --> 04:49.154
It's not a big deal
for a high roller like you.

04:49.156 --> 04:52.357
♪♪

04:52.359 --> 04:54.092
We're done.

04:54.094 --> 04:55.494
Stay away from me.

04:55.496 --> 04:56.829
J, does your family
know about

04:56.831 --> 04:59.031
all the shit
you do on the side?

04:59.033 --> 05:00.432
♪♪

05:00.434 --> 05:02.567
I wonder
what they'd think.

05:02.569 --> 05:04.169
I'm smarter than you.

05:04.171 --> 05:07.506
I have better connections,
better resources.

05:07.508 --> 05:09.174
You just have
a couple of gangbangers

05:09.176 --> 05:10.509
who don't even
like you enough

05:10.511 --> 05:11.776
to give you
a place to sleep.

05:11.778 --> 05:14.646
Yeah?

05:14.648 --> 05:17.249
Smurf have your back?

05:17.251 --> 05:18.450
You sure about that?

05:18.452 --> 05:24.389
♪♪

05:24.391 --> 05:30.328
♪♪

05:30.330 --> 05:33.065
[ Toaster dings ]

05:33.067 --> 05:34.199
Renn: <i> Buenos dias.</i>

05:34.201 --> 05:36.535
Morning.

05:36.537 --> 05:38.537
Ah, I can't stay up that late
anymore.

05:38.539 --> 05:40.004
Pop Tart?

05:40.006 --> 05:42.006
You cooked.
Mm-hmm.

05:42.008 --> 05:43.808
Yeah, there's, uh...

05:43.810 --> 05:44.843
[ Blows on cup ]

05:45.746 --> 05:47.713
There's some coffee, too.

05:49.216 --> 05:50.348
You crashed out here?

05:50.350 --> 05:53.017
Yeah, I couldn't sleep.

05:53.019 --> 05:55.487
[ Phone dings ]
Why's that?

05:55.489 --> 05:57.822
[ Exhales sharply ]
Just stressed out.

05:57.824 --> 06:01.426
Work shit.

06:01.428 --> 06:02.895
Little situation
I'm dealing with.

06:04.164 --> 06:05.163
That the work shit?

06:05.165 --> 06:07.165
Yeah,
I'm waiting on some money.

06:07.167 --> 06:09.434
[ Phone whooshing sound ]

06:09.436 --> 06:10.369
So what's your deal today?

06:10.371 --> 06:12.104
House hunting.

06:12.106 --> 06:13.371
Oh, yeah?

06:13.373 --> 06:14.773
You gonna try and get
something by the beach?

06:14.775 --> 06:16.975
Everything by the beach
is AirBnB now,

06:16.977 --> 06:19.445
and the rest is
in shitty school districts.

06:23.450 --> 06:24.449
Right.

06:24.451 --> 06:25.984
[ Laughs ]

06:25.986 --> 06:27.652
Look, I get it.

06:27.654 --> 06:29.521
I'm pregnant.
It's weird.

06:29.523 --> 06:30.655
No, hey.

06:30.657 --> 06:32.725
No, look, you look...
you look...

06:32.727 --> 06:34.593
You look great.

06:37.131 --> 06:38.230
Thanks.

06:42.937 --> 06:46.471
So, um...

06:46.473 --> 06:47.872
You still have
that connection?

06:47.874 --> 06:49.174
Coke?

06:55.416 --> 06:57.316
[ Phone dings ]

06:59.419 --> 07:02.955
[ Sighs ]

07:02.957 --> 07:06.224
The situation?

07:06.226 --> 07:07.292
Yep.

07:07.294 --> 07:08.160
Hey.

07:11.365 --> 07:12.897
<i>Mi casa es su casa.</i>

07:12.899 --> 07:15.367
♪ <i>...about her past life</i> ♪

07:15.369 --> 07:18.370
♪ <i>It's always hell</i>
<i>with a deep sigh</i> ♪

07:18.372 --> 07:21.640
[ Engine shuts off ]

07:21.642 --> 07:23.441
Jack: Hey, Deran.

07:23.443 --> 07:25.243
Long time, no see.

07:25.245 --> 07:26.511
Your boy's killing it.

07:26.513 --> 07:27.712
He made the final.

07:27.714 --> 07:30.649
Yep.

07:30.651 --> 07:34.519
Always figured it'd be you
on tour, not Adrian.

07:34.521 --> 07:37.289
You out there?
You still selling blow?

07:39.994 --> 07:41.193
Why?
You looking for something?

07:41.195 --> 07:44.529
Is Adrian
working for you?

07:44.531 --> 07:46.731
Is that a problem?

07:46.733 --> 07:48.467
Maybe.

07:48.469 --> 07:49.601
Adrian's a big boy.

07:49.603 --> 07:51.870
Whatever me and him do,
that's our business.

07:53.340 --> 07:54.873
How many times
you been in jail now?

07:54.875 --> 07:56.541
Once, twice?

07:56.543 --> 07:59.812
Three times?

07:59.814 --> 08:02.481
Are you really hassling me
about doing something illegal?

08:02.483 --> 08:04.149
Adrian's got
a solid result now, okay?

08:04.151 --> 08:05.684
You could always
just sponsor him.

08:05.686 --> 08:07.552
Now you're telling me
how to run my business?

08:07.554 --> 08:09.754
If I was telling you
how to run your business,

08:09.756 --> 08:10.622
you'd know about it.

08:12.559 --> 08:13.958
Right?

08:13.960 --> 08:15.127
[ Sniffs ]

08:16.763 --> 08:18.030
Alright.

08:18.032 --> 08:19.764
You should come by the bar
later.

08:19.766 --> 08:21.834
We're watching the final.
I'll buy you a beer.

08:21.836 --> 08:30.843
♪♪

08:30.845 --> 08:39.650
♪♪

08:39.653 --> 08:41.520
Cancer.

08:41.522 --> 08:46.124
♪♪

08:46.126 --> 08:49.928
Doctor told me.

08:49.930 --> 08:51.664
You asked him to.

08:51.666 --> 08:54.066
♪♪

08:54.068 --> 08:57.870
What about my brothers?

08:57.872 --> 08:59.204
What are
you gonna tell them?

08:59.206 --> 09:00.739
I'm not.

09:00.741 --> 09:02.474
And neither are you.

09:02.476 --> 09:05.844
♪♪

09:09.550 --> 09:11.015
Where's Colin?

09:11.017 --> 09:13.552
Uh, I couldn't tell you.

09:13.554 --> 09:15.587
Took his little sidekick Janine
somewhere?

09:19.426 --> 09:21.626
He's tripping out again,
man.

09:21.628 --> 09:22.895
Eh, he's fine.

09:24.231 --> 09:25.597
Give me three.

09:27.101 --> 09:29.501
The guy's cracked, man.

09:29.503 --> 09:31.103
He was at Pinkville,
you know.

09:31.105 --> 09:32.704
Slaughtered babies
and shit.

09:32.706 --> 09:35.173
[ Scoffs ]
He told you that?

09:35.175 --> 09:36.475
He was messing with you.

09:38.445 --> 09:41.045
Yeah, well,
he messes with everyone.

09:41.047 --> 09:42.581
It makes me wonder
who's running this crew.

09:48.455 --> 09:49.922
You got something
to say to me?

09:52.526 --> 09:54.726
I thought I was joining
a professional operation.

09:54.728 --> 09:55.995
That's all.

10:01.135 --> 10:02.935
Listen to me good, Lou.

10:02.937 --> 10:05.404
You're here
because I like you,

10:05.406 --> 10:07.606
because we go way back
and you're funny sometimes,

10:07.608 --> 10:08.607
and that's important.

10:08.609 --> 10:12.210
You also need a big guy,
a bruiser,

10:12.212 --> 10:13.278
someone
who doesn't realize

10:13.280 --> 10:15.147
they're gonna meet
someone bigger someday.

10:15.149 --> 10:17.215
That's Jake.

10:17.217 --> 10:18.417
And you need a guy

10:18.419 --> 10:20.152
who's level-headed
with good ideas.

10:20.154 --> 10:21.153
That's me.

10:21.155 --> 10:23.488
But what you really need

10:23.490 --> 10:26.158
is someone crazy
like Colin,

10:26.160 --> 10:28.026
someone who's gonna
run towards the action

10:28.028 --> 10:29.328
when it's getting hairy.

10:30.831 --> 10:34.099
So, yeah, Lou,
I'll keep you around.

10:34.101 --> 10:36.635
You're funny.

10:36.637 --> 10:37.970
But you better stay
out of the way of

10:37.972 --> 10:39.772
the guy
that I really need.

10:39.774 --> 10:41.840
[ Speaks indistinctly ]

10:41.842 --> 10:43.342
And what
do we need Janine for?

10:47.714 --> 10:52.785
She ain't big,
and she ain't funny.

10:52.787 --> 10:56.021
[ Pours water ]

10:59.193 --> 11:01.326
I need another $20,000

11:01.328 --> 11:04.997
to run through
the Carlsbad house.

11:04.999 --> 11:06.865
Yeah,
I had an emergency.

11:06.867 --> 11:09.601
Doesn't Smurf have a place
you could use?

11:09.603 --> 11:11.403
No.

11:11.405 --> 11:13.338
Better watch out.

11:13.340 --> 11:15.007
Why?

11:15.009 --> 11:16.875
Well, you know, you haven't
been around too much.

11:16.877 --> 11:18.610
And we've noticed.

11:18.612 --> 11:19.812
You don't think Smurf has?

11:19.814 --> 11:21.079
I've been working.

11:21.081 --> 11:22.481
I'm... trying
to find us jobs.

11:22.483 --> 11:25.950
Okay, well, there's trying,
and there's bringing.

11:25.952 --> 11:30.355
There's this movie guy
who's shooting in Morocco.

11:30.357 --> 11:31.824
He owns a bunch of clubs.

11:31.826 --> 11:32.825
Security's tight,

11:32.827 --> 11:34.092
but they're not
professionals.

11:34.094 --> 11:36.161
40-to-60 cash take
on Saturday night.

11:36.163 --> 11:37.629
What do you think?

11:37.631 --> 11:39.364
I like it.
How do you know the guy?

11:39.366 --> 11:40.298
I know his kid.

11:40.300 --> 11:41.766
Okay,
how do you know the kid?

11:41.768 --> 11:43.902
Friend of a friend.

11:46.173 --> 11:48.240
You gonna watch Adrian with us?

11:48.242 --> 11:50.575
You gonna stick around?

11:50.577 --> 11:52.044
[ Sighs ]
I... I can't.

11:52.046 --> 11:53.111
I should go.

11:53.113 --> 11:56.114
Um, think about it,
though.

11:56.116 --> 11:59.518
There you go.
There you go.

11:59.520 --> 12:00.853
Man: <i> These are conditions</i>

12:00.855 --> 12:04.456
<i>that the Oceanside kid</i>
<i>is real comfortable in.</i>

12:04.458 --> 12:06.324
<i>He's got a solid left.</i>

12:06.326 --> 12:07.726
<i>Pumps for some speed,</i>

12:07.728 --> 12:10.529
<i>comes off the bottom solid</i>
<i>into a big first turn,</i>

12:10.531 --> 12:12.197
<i>and then into his second turn.</i>

12:12.199 --> 12:14.132
There you go. <i>The wave
flattens out unfortunately.</i>

12:14.134 --> 12:15.734
Why wasn't he just surfing
like this all the time?

12:15.736 --> 12:17.202
<i>There looks like time to get</i>
<i>the last wave of the set.</i>

12:17.204 --> 12:19.204
<i>Oh, but it's flatter</i>
<i>and a little closed out.</i>

12:19.206 --> 12:20.405
Burying him.

12:20.407 --> 12:21.740
No, no, he's got it.

12:21.742 --> 12:24.008
Alright. Let's hear it.

12:24.010 --> 12:29.414
5, 4, 3, 2, 1...

12:29.416 --> 12:32.484
[ Cheers and applause ] <i>His first
major win of the Four Star Series.</i>

12:32.486 --> 12:33.886
<i>There he is.</i>

12:33.888 --> 12:35.620
[ Cheers and applause ]

12:35.622 --> 12:37.622
Hell, yeah, baby!

12:37.624 --> 12:40.225
Hey, hey, listen up.

12:40.227 --> 12:41.894
Drinks on the house
for now.

12:41.896 --> 12:49.501
[ Cheers and applause ]

12:49.503 --> 12:55.240
[ All chanting "Adrian" ]

12:55.242 --> 13:00.112
♪♪

13:00.114 --> 13:01.680
[ Door opens, closes ]

13:05.452 --> 13:07.586
Angela: Hey.

13:07.588 --> 13:09.188
Feeling better?

13:10.657 --> 13:11.723
Maybe you and Julia

13:11.725 --> 13:13.792
only did the dishes
once a month or so,

13:13.794 --> 13:17.195
but this is
my goddamn house.

13:17.197 --> 13:18.464
You have some respect.

13:21.468 --> 13:22.301
Nope.

13:24.204 --> 13:25.270
[ Scoffs ]

13:28.409 --> 13:30.209
That better?

13:31.411 --> 13:32.477
What's the matter?

13:32.479 --> 13:33.812
Smurf: Nothing.

13:33.814 --> 13:35.147
Angela and I were discussing

13:35.149 --> 13:38.250
the challenges of running
a halfway house for junkies.

13:44.759 --> 13:46.425
[ Exhales ]

13:46.427 --> 13:49.294
I'm out of here.

13:49.296 --> 13:51.363
That's your dead sister
she's talking about,

13:51.365 --> 13:52.897
you know that, right?

13:52.899 --> 13:54.699
[ Sighs ]

13:54.701 --> 13:57.169
Just... stop.

13:57.171 --> 13:58.102
[ Exhales sharply ]

13:58.104 --> 13:59.371
Please stop.

13:59.373 --> 14:00.639
I'm not an idiot.

14:00.641 --> 14:02.507
Neither of you
want me here.

14:02.509 --> 14:03.976
I want you here.

14:03.978 --> 14:05.844
[ Dishes, silverware
clattering in distance ]

14:05.846 --> 14:09.782
Yeah, well,
it's her house.

14:09.784 --> 14:11.583
It's my house, too.

14:11.585 --> 14:12.785
Shit.

14:12.787 --> 14:15.654
[ Scoffs ]

14:15.656 --> 14:16.922
No, you're not leaving.

14:18.459 --> 14:20.626
Just put your stuff
in Craig's old room.

14:22.129 --> 14:23.429
Okay?

14:26.467 --> 14:27.932
Get her out of here.

14:27.934 --> 14:29.234
She stays.

14:30.404 --> 14:32.070
This is the bitch

14:32.072 --> 14:34.673
that got your sister
strung out on smack.

14:34.675 --> 14:37.542
[ Quietly ]
You want me here, right?

14:37.544 --> 14:40.612
You want me
to keep my mouth shut?

14:40.614 --> 14:42.146
She stays.

14:42.148 --> 14:49.421
♪♪

14:49.423 --> 14:52.157
♪♪

14:52.159 --> 14:53.358
Sir.
Thank you.

